This section describes warpgroup level `wgmma.mma_async` instruction and the organization of
various matrices involved in this instruction.

##### 9.7.15.5.1. [Register Fragments and Shared Memory Matrix Layouts](#asynchronous-warpgroup-level-matrix-fragment)

The input matrix A of the warpgroup wide MMA operations can be either in registers or in the shared
memory. The input matrix B of the warpgroup wide MMA operations must be in the shared memory. This
section describes the layouts of register fragments and shared memory expected by the warpgroup MMA
instructions.

When the matrices are in shared memory, their starting addresses must be aligned to 16 bytes.

###### 9.7.15.5.1.1. [Register Fragments](#asynchronous-warpgroup-level-matrix-register-fragment)

This section describes the organization of various matrices located in register operands of the
`wgmma.mma_async` instruction.

###### 9.7.15.5.1.1.1. [Matrix Fragments for `wgmma.mma_async.m64nNk16`](#asynchronous-warpgroup-level-matrix-register-fragment-wgmma-64n16)

A warpgroup executing `wgmma.mma_async.m64nNk16` will compute an MMA operation of shape
`.m64nNk16` where N is a valid `n` dimension as listed in
[Matrix Shape](#asynchronous-warpgroup-level-matrix-shape).

Elements of the matrix are distributed across the threads in a warpgroup so each thread of the
warpgroup holds a fragment of the matrix.

* Multiplicand A in registers:

  | .atype | Fragment | Elements (low to high) |
  | --- | --- | --- |
  | `.f16`/`.bf16` | A vector expression containing four `.f16x2` registers, with each register containing two `.f16`/ `.bf16` elements from matrix A. | a0, a1, a2, a3, a4, a5, a6, a7 |

  The layout of the fragments held by different threads is shown in [Figure 148](#wgmma-64n16-a).



[Figure: wgmma-64N16-A]
WGMMA .m64nNk16 Register Fragment Layout for Matrix A

OVERVIEW:
- Instruction: WGMMA (Warpgroup Matrix Multiply Accumulate)
- Matrix dimensions: M=64, N=N (variable), K=16
- This figure describes Matrix A
- The x-axis label is "R\C" (Row \ Column), with columns 0-15
- The y-axis represents matrix rows 0-63
- The bottom label reads: "(tid % 128) : fragments"
- Thread IDs are referenced as T0, T1, ..., T127 (and beyond), using tid % 128

GRID STRUCTURE:
- Columns 0-15 represent the K dimension (16 elements wide)
- Rows 0-63 represent the M dimension (64 rows)
- The table is divided into left half (columns 0-7) and right half (columns 8-15)
- Rows are grouped into 4 color-coded warpgroup sections:
  - Rows 0-15: Blue (first warpgroup, threads T0-T31)
  - Rows 16-31: Orange/Salmon (second warpgroup, threads T32-T63)
  - Rows 32-47: Green (third warpgroup, threads T64-T95)
  - Rows 48-63: Purple/Pink (fourth warpgroup, threads T96-T127)

DATA TYPE:
- Elements are labeled a0, a1, a2, a3, a4, a5, a6, a7
- Two elements are packed per register entry (e.g., {a0, a1}), indicating 16-bit elements (f16 or bf16) packed two per 32-bit register
- Each thread holds 4 registers total: {a0,a1}, {a2,a3}, {a4,a5}, {a6,a7}

COLUMN GROUPING:
- Columns 0-7 (left half): threads hold registers {a0,a1} or {a2,a3}
- Columns 8-15 (right half): threads hold registers {a4,a5} or {a6,a7}

DETAILED LAYOUT BY ROW AND THREAD:

BLUE SECTION (Matrix rows 0-15, tid % 128 = T0-T31):

Row 0 (matrix row 0):
  Columns 0-1: T0:{a0, a1}
  Columns 2-3: T1:{a0, a1}
  Columns 4-5: T2:{a0, a1}
  Columns 6-7: T3:{a0, a1}
  Columns 8-9: T0:{a4, a5}
  Columns 10-11: T1:{a4, a5}
  Columns 12-13: T2:{a4, a5}
  Columns 14-15: T3:{a4, a5}

Row 1 (matrix row 1):
  Columns 0-1: T4:{a0, a1}
  Columns 2-3: T5:{a0, a1}
  Columns 4-5: T6:{a0, a1}
  Columns 6-7: T7:{a0, a1}
  Columns 8-9: T4:{a4, a5}
  Columns 10-11: T5:{a4, a5}
  Columns 12-13: T6:{a4, a5}
  Columns 14-15: T7:{a4, a5}

Rows 2-6: Continue pattern (T8-T27, incrementing by 4 threads per row, each holding {a0,a1} left / {a4,a5} right)

Row 7 (matrix row 7):
  Columns 0-1: T28:{a0, a1}
  Columns 2-3: T29:{a0, a1}
  Columns 4-5: T30:{a0, a1}
  Columns 6-7: T31:{a0, a1}
  Columns 8-9: T28:{a4, a5}
  Columns 10-11: T29:{a4, a5}
  Columns 12-13: T30:{a4, a5}
  Columns 14-15: T31:{a4, a5}

Row 8 (matrix row 8):
  Columns 0-1: T0:{a2, a3}
  Columns 2-3: T1:{a2, a3}
  Columns 4-5: T2:{a2, a3}
  Columns 6-7: T3:{a2, a3}
  Columns 8-9: T0:{a6, a7}
  Columns 10-11: T1:{a6, a7}
  Columns 12-13: T2:{a6, a7}
  Columns 14-15: T3:{a6, a7}

Rows 9-14: Continue pattern (T4-T27, incrementing by 4 threads per row, each holding {a2,a3} left / {a6,a7} right)

Row 15 (matrix row 15):
  Columns 0-1: T28:{a2, a3}
  Columns 2-3: T29:{a2, a3}
  Columns 4-5: T30:{a2, a3}
  Columns 6-7: T31:{a2, a3}
  Columns 8-9: T28:{a6, a7}
  Columns 10-11: T29:{a6, a7}
  Columns 12-13: T30:{a6, a7}
  Columns 14-15: T31:{a6, a7}

ORANGE SECTION (Matrix rows 16-31, tid % 128 = T32-T63):

Row 16 (matrix row 16):
  Columns 0-1: T32:{a0, a1}
  Columns 2-3: T33:{a0, a1}
  Columns 4-5: T34:{a0, a1}
  Columns 6-7: T35:{a0, a1}
  Columns 8-9: T32:{a4, a5}
  Columns 10-11: T33:{a4, a5}
  Columns 12-13: T34:{a4, a5}
  Columns 14-15: T35:{a4, a5}

Rows 17-30: Continue pattern (T36-T59, incrementing by 4 threads per row)
  Rows 16-23: threads hold {a0,a1} left / {a4,a5} right
  Rows 24-31: threads hold {a2,a3} left / {a6,a7} right

Row 31 (matrix row 31):
  Columns 0-1: T60:{a2, a3}
  Columns 2-3: T61:{a2, a3}
  Columns 4-5: T62:{a2, a3}
  Columns 6-7: T63:{a2, a3}
  Columns 8-9: T60:{a6, a7}
  Columns 10-11: T61:{a6, a7}
  Columns 12-13: T62:{a6, a7}
  Columns 14-15: T63:{a6, a7}

GREEN SECTION (Matrix rows 32-47, tid % 128 = T64-T95):

Row 32 (matrix row 32):
  Columns 0-1: T64:{a0, a1}
  Columns 2-3: T65:{a0, a1}
  Columns 4-5: T66:{a0, a1}
  Columns 6-7: T67:{a0, a1}
  Columns 8-9: T64:{a4, a5}
  Columns 10-11: T65:{a4, a5}
  Columns 12-13: T66:{a4, a5}
  Columns 14-15: T67:{a4, a5}

Rows 33-46: Continue pattern (T68-T91, incrementing by 4 threads per row)
  Rows 32-39: threads hold {a0,a1} left / {a4,a5} right
  Rows 40-47: threads hold {a2,a3} left / {a6,a7} right

Row 47 (matrix row 47):
  Columns 0-1: T92:{a2, a3}
  Columns 2-3: T93:{a2, a3}
  Columns 4-5: T94:{a2, a3}
  Columns 6-7: T95:{a2, a3}
  Columns 8-9: T92:{a6, a7}
  Columns 10-11: T93:{a6, a7}
  Columns 12-13: T94:{a6, a7}
  Columns 14-15: T95:{a6, a7}

PURPLE SECTION (Matrix rows 48-63, tid % 128 = T96-T127):

Row 48 (matrix row 48):
  Columns 0-1: T96:{a0, a1}
  Columns 2-3: T97:{a0, a1}
  Columns 4-5: T98:{a0, a1}
  Columns 6-7: T99:{a0, a1}
  Columns 8-9: T96:{a4, a5}
  Columns 10-11: T97:{a4, a5}
  Columns 12-13: T98:{a4, a5}
  Columns 14-15: T99:{a4, a5}

Rows 49-62: Continue pattern (T100-T123, incrementing by 4 threads per row)
  Rows 48-55: threads hold {a0,a1} left / {a4,a5} right


  Figure 148 WGMMA .m64nNk16 register fragment layout for matrix A.
* Accumulator D:

  | .dtype | Fragment | Elements (low to high) |
  | --- | --- | --- |
  | `.f16` | A vector expression containing N/4 number of `.f16x2` registers, with each register containing two `.f16` elements from matrix D. | d0, d1, d2, d3, …, dX, dY, dZ, dW  where `X = N/2  -  4`  `Y = N/2  -  3`  `Z = N/2  -  2`  `W = N/2  -  1`  `N = 8*i where i = {1, 2, ... , 32}` |
  | `.f32` | A vector expression containing N/2 number of `.f32` registers. |

  The layout of the fragments held by different threads is shown in [Figure 149](#wgmma-64n16-d).



[Figure: wgmma-64N16-D]
WGMMA .m64nNk16 Accumulator Matrix D Register Fragment Layout

OVERVIEW
Matrix: D (accumulator)
Operation dimensions: M=64, N=N (variable), K=16
The figure uses thread IDs (tid) modulo 128, meaning the warpgroup has 128 threads (T0 through T127).
The label at the bottom reads: (tid % 128) : fragments

GRID STRUCTURE
Rows (R): Matrix rows 0 through 63
Columns (C): Matrix columns 0 through N-1, shown in groups: 0-7, 8-15, ..., N-8 to N-1
Each cell shows: ThreadID:{register_elements}

DATA TYPE
The accumulator elements are labeled d0, d1, d2, d3, d4, d5, d6, d7, dX, dY, dZ, dW.
Each thread holds pairs of elements per cell (e.g., {d0, d1}), indicating two accumulator values packed per register entry or two registers per cell.
The data type is not explicitly labeled in the figure but given the WGMMA context and accumulator role, these are .f32 values (one per register) or .f16 pairs. Given the pairing notation {d0,d1}, these are likely .f16 or .f32 pairs stored in consecutive registers.

COLOR-CODED ROW GROUPS (by thread block / warp)
Rows 0-7 and 8-15: Light blue background, threads T0-T31 (rows 0-7) and T0-T31 (rows 8-15)
Rows 16-23 and 24-31: Orange/tan background, threads T32-T63
Rows 32-39 and 40-47: Green background, threads T64-T95
Rows 48-55 and 56-63: Purple/pink background, threads T96-T127

DETAILED ELEMENT MAPPING BY ROW AND COLUMN GROUP

ROWS 0-7 (light blue, upper half of first warp group):

Row 0, Columns 0-3: T0:{d0,d1}, T1:{d0,d1}, T2:{d0,d1}, T3:{d0,d1}
Row 0, Columns 4-7: (continuation via arrow, same threads T0-T3)
Row 0, Columns 8-11: T0:{d4,d5}, T1:{d4,d5}, T2:{d4,d5}, T3:{d4,d5}
Row 0, Columns 12-15: T0:{d4,d5}, T1:{d4,d5}, T2:{d4,d5}, T3:{d4,d5}
Row 0, Columns N-8 to N-5: T0:{dX,dY}, T1:{dX,dY}, T2:{dX,dY}, T3:{dX,dY}
Row 0, Columns N-4 to N-1: T0:{dX,dY}, T1:{dX,dY}, T2:{dX,dY}, T3:{dX,dY}

Row 1, Columns 0-3: T4:{d0,d1}, T5:{d0,d1}, T6:{d0,d1}, T7:{d0,d1}
Row 1, Columns 8-11: T4:{d4,d5}, T5:{d4,d5}, T6:{d4,d5}, T7:{d4,d5}
Row 1, Columns N-8 to N-5: T4:{dX,dY}, T5:{dX,dY}, T6:{dX,dY}, T7:{dX,dY}

Rows 2-6: implied by arrows (same pattern continues with T8-T27 in groups of 4)

Row 7, Columns 0-3: T28:{d0,d1}, T29:{d0,d1}, T30:{d0,d1}, T31:{d0,d1}
Row 7, Columns 8-11: T28:{d4,d5}, T29:{d4,d5}, T30:{d4,d5}, T31:{d4,d5}
Row 7, Columns N-8 to N-5: T28:{dX,dY}, T29:{dX,dY}, T30:{dX,dY}, T31:{dX,dY}

ROWS 8-15 (light blue, lower half of first warp group):

Row 8, Columns 0-3: T0:{d2,d3}, T1:{d2,d3}, T2:{d2,d3}, T3:{d2,d3}
Row 8, Columns 8-11: T0:{d6,d7}, T1:{d6,d7}, T2:{d6,d7}, T3:{d6,d7}
Row 8, Columns N-8 to N-5: T0:{dZ,dW}, T1:{dZ,dW}, T2:{dZ,dW}, T3:{dZ,dW}

Rows 9-14: implied by arrows (T4-T27 in groups of 4, same pattern)

Row 15, Columns 0-3: T28:{d2,d3}, T29:{d2,d3}, T30:{d2,d3}, T31:{d2,d3}
Row 15, Columns 8-11: T28:{d6,d7}, T29:{d6,d7}, T30:{d6,d7}, T31:{d6,d7}
Row 15, Columns N-8 to N-5: T28:{dZ,dW}, T29:{dZ,dW}, T30:{dZ,dW}, T31:{dZ,dW}

ROWS 16-31 (orange/tan, second warp group, threads T32-T63):

Row 16, Columns 0-3: T32:{d0,d1}, T33:{d0,d1}, T34:{d0,d1}, T35:{d0,d1}
Row 16, Columns 8-11: T32:{d4,d5}, T33:{d4,d5}, T34:{d4,d5}, T35:{d4,d5}
Row 16, Columns N-8 to N-5: T32:{dX,dY}, T33:{dX,dY}, T34:{dX,dY}, T35:{dX,dY}

Rows 17-22: implied (T36-T59 in groups of 4)

Row 23 (shown as row with ..): implied continuation

Row 31, Columns 0-3: T60:{d2,d3}, T61:{d2,d3}, T62:{d2,d3}, T63:{d2,d3}
Row 31, Columns 8-11: T60:{d6,d7}, T61:{d6,d7}, T62:{d6,d7}, T63:{d6,d7}
Row 31, Columns N-8 to N-5: T60:{dZ,dW}, T61:{dZ,dW}, T62:{dZ,dW}, T63:{dZ,dW}

Note: Rows 16-23 use {d0,d1} and {d4,d5} (upper sub-block), rows 24-31 use {d2,d3} and {d6,d7} (lower sub-block), same as the rows 0-7 / 8-15 pattern.

ROWS 32-47 (green, third warp group, threads T64-T95):

Row 32, Columns 0-3: T64:{d0,d1}, T65:{d0,d1}, T66:{d0,d1}, T67:{d0,d1}
Row 32, Columns 8-11: T64:{d4,d5}, T65:{d4,d5}, T66:{d4,d5}, T67:{d4,d5}
Row 32, Columns N-8 to N-5: T64:{dX,dY}, T65:{dX,dY}, T66:{dX,dY}, T67:{dX,dY}

Rows 33-38: implied (T68-T91 in groups of 4)

Row 39 (shown as ..): implied

Row 47, Columns 0-3: T92:{d2,d3}, T93:{d2,d3}, T94:{d2,d3}, T95:{d2,d3}
Row 47, Columns 8-11: T92:{d6,d7}, T93:{d6,d7}, T94:{d6,d7}, T95:{d6,d7}
Row 47, Columns N-8 to N-5: T92:{dZ,dW}, T93:{dZ,dW}, T94:{dZ,dW}, T95:{dZ,dW}

ROWS 48-63 (purple/pink, fourth warp group, threads T96-T127):

Row 48, Columns 0-3: T96:{d0,d1}, T97:{d0,d1}, T98:{d0,d1}, T99:{d0,d1}
Row 48, Columns 8-11: T96:{d4,d5}, T97:{d4,d5}, T98:{d4,d5}, T99:{d4,d5}
Row 48, Columns N-8 to N-5: T96:{dX,dY}, T97:{dX,dY}, T98:{dX,dY}, T99:{dX,dY}

Rows 49-54: implied (T100-T123 in groups of 4)

Row 55 (shown as ..): implied

Row 63, Columns 0-3: T124:{d2,d3}, T125:{d2,d3}, T126:{d2,d3}, T127:{d2,d3}
Row 63, Columns 8-11: T124:{d6,d7}, T125:{


  Figure 149 WGMMA .m64nNk16 register fragment layout for accumulator matrix D.

###### 9.7.15.5.1.1.2. [Matrix Fragments for `wgmma.mma_async.m64nNk8`](#asynchronous-warpgroup-level-matrix-register-fragment-wgmma-64n8)

A warpgroup executing `wgmma.mma_async.m64nNk8` will compute an MMA operation of shape
`.m64nNk8` where N is a valid `n` dimension as listed in [Matrix Shape](#asynchronous-warpgroup-level-matrix-shape).

Elements of the matrix are distributed across the threads in a warpgroup so each thread of the
warpgroup holds a fragment of the matrix.

* Multiplicand A in registers:

  | .atype | Fragment | Elements (low to high) |
  | --- | --- | --- |
  | `.tf32` | A vector expression containing four `.b32` registers containing four `.tf32` elements from matrix A. | a0, a1, a2, a3 |

  The layout of the fragments held by different threads is shown in [Figure 150](#wgmma-64n8-a).



[Figure: wgmma-64N8-A]
WGMMA .m64nNk8 Register Fragment Layout for Matrix A

OVERVIEW:
- Instruction: WGMMA .m64nNk8
- Matrix: A (input matrix)
- Matrix dimensions: M=64, K=8 (the N dimension varies, this figure shows the A matrix fragment)
- Total threads involved: 128 threads (T0 through T127), addressed as tid % 128
- Each thread holds 4 register elements: a0, a1, a2, a3
- The figure axes: R\C where R = matrix row (0-63), C = column index (0-7) representing thread/register positions

GRID STRUCTURE:
- Rows (R): 0 through 63 — these are the 64 rows of matrix A
- Columns (C): 0 through 7 — these represent 8 positions across the warpgroup
- The columns are split into two groups: C0-C3 (left half) and C4-C7 (right half)
- The row axis is labeled "(tid % 128) : fragments" at the bottom

DATA TYPE:
- The layout is consistent with .f16 or .bf16 (two 16-bit values packed per 32-bit register), giving 4 register slots (a0, a1, a2, a3) per thread for K=8 (8 elements / 2 per register = 4 registers)

REGISTER ELEMENT MAPPING:
- a0 and a1 correspond to columns C0-C3 (left block)
- a2 and a3 correspond to columns C4-C7 (right block)
- a0 covers matrix rows 0-7 (and repeating pattern rows 16-31, 32-47, 48-63 for higher thread groups)
- a1 covers matrix rows 8-15 (and repeating pattern)
- a2 covers matrix rows 0-7 (right K-half)
- a3 covers matrix rows 8-15 (right K-half)

COLOR-CODED THREAD GROUPS (4 groups of 32 threads each):

GROUP 1 (Blue): Threads T0-T31 (tid 0-31), handles matrix rows 0-15
  Rows 0-7, Columns 0-3: register a0
    Row 0:  T0:a0,  T1:a0,  T2:a0,  T3:a0
    Row 1:  T4:a0,  T5:a0,  T6:a0,  T7:a0
    ...continuing pattern (T0-T31 each appear once in rows 0-7 for a0)
    Row 7:  T28:a0, T29:a0, T30:a0, T31:a0

  Rows 0-7, Columns 4-7: register a2
    Row 0:  T0:a2,  T1:a2,  T2:a2,  T3:a2
    Row 1:  T4:a2,  T5:a2,  T6:a2,  T7:a2
    ...
    Row 7:  T28:a2, T29:a2, T30:a2, T31:a2

  Rows 8-15, Columns 0-3: register a1
    Row 8:  T0:a1,  T1:a1,  T2:a1,  T3:a1
    ...
    Row 15: T28:a1, T29:a1, T30:a1, T31:a1

  Rows 8-15, Columns 4-7: register a3
    Row 8:  T0:a3,  T1:a3,  T2:a3,  T3:a3
    ...
    Row 15: T28:a3, T29:a3, T30:a3, T31:a3

GROUP 2 (Peach/Orange): Threads T32-T63 (tid 32-63), handles matrix rows 16-31
  Rows 16-23, Columns 0-3: register a0
    Row 16: T32:a0, T33:a0, T34:a0, T35:a0
    ...
    Row 31: T60:a1, T61:a1, T62:a1, T63:a1

  Rows 16-23, Columns 4-7: register a2
    Row 16: T32:a2, T33:a2, T34:a2, T35:a2
    ...

  Rows 24-31, Columns 0-3: register a1
    Row 31: T60:a1, T61:a1, T62:a1, T63:a1

  Rows 24-31, Columns 4-7: register a3
    Row 31: T60:a3, T61:a3, T62:a3, T63:a3

GROUP 3 (Green): Threads T64-T95 (tid 64-95), handles matrix rows 32-47
  Rows 32-39, Columns 0-3: register a0
    Row 32: T64:a0, T65:a0, T66:a0, T67:a0
    ...
    Row 47: T92:a1, T93:a1, T94:a1, T95:a1

  Rows 32-39, Columns 4-7: register a2
    Row 32: T64:a2, T65:a2, T66:a2, T67:a2
    ...

  Rows 40-47, Columns 0-3: register a1
    Row 47: T92:a1, T93:a1, T94:a1, T95:a1

  Rows 40-47, Columns 4-7: register a3
    Row 47: T92:a3, T93:a3, T94:a3, T95:a3

GROUP 4 (Purple/Lavender): Threads T96-T127 (tid 96-127), handles matrix rows 48-63
  Rows 48-55, Columns 0-3: register a0
    Row 48:  T96:a0,  T97:a0,  T98:a0,  T99:a0
    ...
    Row 63: T124:a1, T125:a1, T126:a1, T127:a1

  Rows 48-55, Columns 4-7: register a2
    Row 48:  T96:a2,  T97:a2,  T98:a2,  T99:a2
    ...

  Rows 56-63, Columns 0-3: register a1
    Row 63: T124:a1, T125:a1, T126:a1, T127:a1

  Rows 56-63, Columns 4-7: register a3
    Row 63: T124:a3, T125:a3, T126:a3, T127:a3

THREAD-TO-ROW MAPPING PATTERN (within each group of 32 threads):
- Within each 16-row block, threads are assigned 4 per row
- Threads increment by 4 per row: rows 0,1,2,...7 use threads {0-3},{4-7},{8-11},{12-15},{16-19},{20-23},{24-27},{28-31} (offset by group base)
- Each thread appears exactly once in the 8-row sub-block for each register (a0 or a1)

PACKING SUMMARY:
- Each thread holds exactly 4 register fragments: a0, a1, a2, a3
- a0 and a1 hold the left K-half (columns 0-3 of the K=8 dimension), packed as two 16-bit values per 32-bit register
- a2 and a3 hold the right K-half (columns 4-7 of the K=8 dimension), packed as two 16-bit values per 32-bit register
- a0 covers the first 8 rows of the thread group's assigned row range
- a1 covers the second 8 rows of the thread group's assigned row range
- The 128 threads collectively cover all 64 rows of matrix A across K=8 columns


  Figure 150 WGMMA .m64nNk8 register fragment layout for matrix A.
* Accumulator D:

  | .dtype | Fragment | Elements (low to high) |
  | --- | --- | --- |
  | `.f32` | A vector expression containing N/2 number of `.f32` registers. | d0, d1, d2, d3, …, dX, dY, dZ, dW  where `X = N/2  -  4`  `Y = N/2  -  3`  `Z = N/2  -  2`  `W = N/2  -  1`  `N = 8*i where i = {1, 2, ... , 32}` |

  The layout of the fragments held by different threads is shown in [Figure 151](#wgmma-64n8-d).



[Figure: wgmma-64N8-D]
WGMMA .m64nNk8 Accumulator Matrix D Register Fragment Layout

OVERVIEW
Matrix: D (accumulator)
Operation shape: M=64, N=N (variable), K=8
This figure shows the full warpgroup (128 threads, T0-T127) layout.
The x-axis (columns) represents matrix column indices 0 through N-1.
The y-axis (rows) represents matrix row indices 0 through 63.
